            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/payables/batches","startButtonLabel":"Tour Payment Batches","steps":[{"element":".tab-bar","popover":{"title":"The Batches Tab","description":"The Batches tab shows only when an administrator has turned on bank payments and you are an Admin, Manager, or Office Manager. It turns approved bank-transfer payments into a NACHA file you upload to your bank portal.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-testid='new-payment-batch-btn']","popover":{"title":"New Batch","description":"Click here to assemble a batch. The panel asks for an effective date (when funds should settle) and lists every eligible ACH payment. Check the ones to include; the selected total updates as you go. Click Assemble Batch to create it as a Draft.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-testid='new-prenote-batch-btn']","popover":{"title":"Prenote Batch","description":"A Prenote Batch sends a zero-dollar verification entry to every approved, not-yet-prenoted vendor bank account. You generate, download, and upload it like any batch; after the bank's return window passes, mark those accounts Verified on the Accounts tab.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"[data-testid='import-returns-btn']","popover":{"title":"Import Returns File","description":"After the bank processes a file, it sends back returns (rejected payments) and Notification of Change (NOC) entries. Click here and choose the bank's file (.ach, .txt, or .dat) to apply them. The import is idempotent and reports returned payments, rejected prenotes, and correction notices.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"The Batches Table","description":"Each row is a batch. You see its number, a status label (Draft, Generated, Released, or Cancelled), a Prenote label on prenote batches, the entry count, total, effective date, and who created and released it. The buttons on each row change with the status.","side":"top"}},{"element":"app-data-table","popover":{"title":"Generate, Download, Release, Cancel","description":"On a Draft batch: Generate NACHA file (build icon) or Cancel. On a Generated batch: Download file, Release, or Cancel. Release confirms the file was uploaded and marks the payments transmitted — and must be done by a different user than the batch creator (segregation of duties).","side":"top"}}]}"""
